		<h3>Training</h3>
		<h4>Architecture Reference for Cooperative & Intelligent Transportation (ARC-IT) Training</h4>
		<p>
			The U.S. Department of Transportation (USDOT) offers 
			<a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/arcitwebtraining.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">training material</a> accompanying its 
			<a href="https://www.arc-it.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Architecture Reference for Cooperative and Intelligent Transportation (ARC-IT)</a>, 
			the <a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/radit.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Regional Architecture Development for Intelligent Transportation (RAD-IT)</a> and 
			the <a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/setit.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Systems Engineering Tool for Intelligent Transportation (SET-IT)</a>. 
			RAD-IT supports development of regional and project ITS architectures using ARC-IT as a starting point. SET-IT integrates drawing and
			database tools with ARC-IT so that users can develop detailed ITS project architectures. ARC-IT and the accompanying tool
			sets help implementers develop architectures to effectively meet their needs and facilitate efficient, secure, and
			interoperable ITS deployments. The online training courses are available directly from the ARC-IT website, providing
			students with an understanding of how to navigate and use 
			<a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/arcitwebtraining.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ARC-IT</a>, 
			use the software tools <a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/raditwebtraining.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RAD-IT</a> & 
			<a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/setitwebtraining.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SET-IT</a>, and how to 
			<a href="https://www.arc-it.net/html/resources/useandmainttraining.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Use & Maintain</a> a 
			regional ITS architecture.
		</p>
		<h4>ITS Standards Training Modules</h4>
		<p>
			<a href="https://www.its.dot.gov/pcb/stds_training.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ITS Standards Training Modules</a> are 
			aimed at practitioners in state and local highway agencies and transit agencies who
			seek the skills needed to procure, implement, and operate ITS standards-based devices and equipment.
			<ul>
				<li>
					The <strong>60-module training series</strong> is for practitioners in state and local highway agencies and transit agencies who seek
					the skills needed to procure, test, implement, and operate standards-based ITS systems and devices. Consultants,
					system designers, integrators, and testers will also find the training informative.
				</li>
				<li>
					The <strong>26-module transit training series</strong> focuses exclusively on standards used in transit applications. Similar to the 60-
					modules series, the transit modules give practitioners the skills to help them effectively procure and utilize standards
					used in transit systems and devices.
				</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
